.alert.alert-info.mb-0
  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Ultimate goal
  %p.mb-3
    Set every ability milestone level for one teammate in a single pass—usually to catch them up after onboarding or when you are new to OG—then review and save once.

  %h6.fw-semibold.mb-2 When to use this page
  %p.mb-2
    %strong Use it once per person.
    Either you are new to OG and awarding milestones for someone who has already demonstrated confidence and competency in the Abilities below, or this is a new hire around their 90-day mark and you are catching them up from what you have observed.
  %p.mb-3
    %strong Warning:
    Milestones are meant to be awarded forever. They can be removed, but that is an anti-pattern in OG. Only award when you are confident. If you are uncertain, set a goal for that Ability and Teammate instead, and wait to award the Milestone until the goal is complete.

  %h6.fw-semibold.mb-2 How to read each row
  %ul.mb-3
    %li
      %strong Ability
      — name links to that teammate’s ability page; hover milestone buttons for milestone detail popovers.
    %li
      %strong Milestone level (0–5)
      — the selected level is the target after save. Level
      %strong 0
      clears every attainment for that ability. Choosing a higher level also creates any missing lower milestones (for example, 3 adds 1 and 2 if they are missing).
    %li
      %strong Sources
      — expand to see assignments or position blueprints that require this ability and at what level.

  .row
    .col-12.col-lg-6
      %h6.fw-semibold.mb-2 Milestone level controls
      %ul.mb-0
        %li
          %span.btn.btn-sm.btn-outline-secondary.me-2 0
          Clear all milestones for this ability on this teammate.
        %li
          %span.btn.btn-sm.btn-outline-primary.me-2 1
          %span.btn.btn-sm.btn-outline-primary.me-2 2
          Award up to that level (fills in any missing lower levels automatically).
    .col-12.col-lg-6
      %h6.fw-semibold.mb-2 Before you save
      %ul.mb-0
        %li
          Use
          %strong Review changes before making them
          to confirm additions, removals, and which new levels will be company-visible.
        %li
          Prefer awarding one milestone at a time from Celebrate milestones when you are not doing a deliberate catch-up pass.
